# Cursor Rules — steaksoap

## Project
React 19 + TypeScript + Vite 7 + Tailwind CSS 4 (CSS-first via @theme) + pnpm.
AI-first React starter kit for vibe coders. Mobile-first. Strict TypeScript (no `any`).

## Architecture
Path aliases: @components/, @hooks/, @pages/, @utils/, @config/, @data/, @types/, @constants/, @lib/, @assets/, @app/, @context/, @styles/
Never use relative imports like `../../..`.

```
src/
├── app/          → Routes, layouts
├── components/
│   ├── ui/       → Atoms (Button, Card…)
│   ├── layout/   → Header, Footer, Nav…
│   └── features/ → Feature components
├── config/       → Cloudinary, SEO, env
├── pages/        → One page = one route
├── hooks/        → Custom hooks
├── utils/        → Pure functions
├── types/        → Shared types
├── data/         → Static data
└── styles/       → Fonts, animations, @theme tokens
```

## Code Style
- Functional components only. Named exports for non-page components, default exports for pages.
- Tailwind utility classes. Design tokens via `@theme` in index.css (bg-bg, text-fg, text-accent, text-muted).
- `cn()` from @utils for conditional classes: `cn('base', condition && 'active', className)`.
- Mobile-first: code for 375px, then `sm:`, `md:`, `lg:`.
- Every component: comment block at top explaining its purpose.

## Git Conventions
- Conventional Commits: `type(scope): description` (lowercase, imperative, <72 chars)
- Types: feat, fix, refactor, style, chore, docs, perf, test
- Branch naming: `type/scope` (e.g., `feat/gallery-grid`)
- Never commit to main directly. Always branch → merge --no-ff.

## Validation
Run `pnpm validate` (lint + typecheck + test + build) before any merge.
Zero errors required. No console.log in production code.

## Key Files
- CLAUDE.md — Full AI workflow instructions
- src/index.css — Design tokens (@theme block)
- src/config/env.ts — Environment variables (all optional with fallbacks)
- src/config/site.ts — Site metadata (name, URL, SEO)
